    <text>
        <body>
            <div xml:id="d.1">
                <head type="title">Miklós Oláh to János Czeglédi (Brussels, 9 March 1533)</head>
                <floatingText type="regesta">
                    <body>
                        <p xml:id="reg.p.1">In his letter of 10 February he wrote everything
                            Czeglédi needs to know. Czeglédi should see Schepper, he can consult
                            him, and based on his advice he should speak with Brodarics and Nádasdy.
                            Sarson will help if he needs money. He should pay attention and be
                            careful. He can talk freely with Brodarics, they used to be good
                            friends.</p>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
                <pb facs="15330309_2_1.jpg"/>
                <p xml:id="p.1">Ad Ioannem Cegledinum provisorem.</p>
                <p xml:id="p.2">Tam multis <add corresp="Olahus" type="insert">a</add> die
                        decima<note xml:id="note.1">We only know Oláh’s long letter on 18 February,
                        see Ep. 325, so either Oláh did not remember the precise day, or he sent
                        another letter.<ref>olahus.tei.15330218_2</ref></note> mensis Februarii
                    praeteriti ad te in rebus meis scripsi, ut non putem nunc mihi necessarium esse
                    plura scribere. In me nihil defuit, quin de omnibus meis te docerem, quae in his
                    recuperandis essent agenda. Vide ergo, ne in te quoque aliquid desit, quod non
                    diligenter istic <del corresp="Olahus">esses</del><add corresp="Olahus"
                        type="corr">sis</add> exsecuturus. <persName>Cornelius Sceperus</persName>
                    orator caesaris istic est. Accede eum,<note xml:id="note.2">See Ep. 337. Cap.
                            3.<ref>olahus.tei.15330309_1</ref></note> cum eo tuto loqui et eius
                    etiam consilium sequi poteris. Ipse si res in partem adversam casu caderet, uti
                    tibi litteris <del corresp="Olahus">ipsi</del> meis aliis scripseram, omnem
                    interponet suam operam, ea via, quam ipse scit et ego intelligo. Cuius consilio
                    etiam <add corresp="Olahus" type="insert">cum</add><persName>Stephano
                        doctore</persName><note xml:id="note.3">István Brodarics.</note> et
                        <persName>Nadasdi</persName>, si opus erit, agere poteris ad recuperationem
                    bonorum nostrorum. Ad exsecutionem aliam pecuniam, quam poterit, suppeditabit
                    tibi, si aliunde interea nullam contrahere poteris, <persName>Andreas
                        Sarson</persName>.<note xml:id="note.4">See Ep. 325. Note
                            19.<ref>olahus.tei.15330218_2</ref></note> Ex villa
                        <placeName>Tharcz</placeName><note xml:id="note.5">Nová Lipnica, see <hi
                            rend="smallcap">C. Tóth–Lakatos–Mikó</hi> 2014, 172.</note> quoque ex
                    cathedratice et quarta<note xml:id="note.6">The Chapter of Bratislava was able
                        to collect and posses a quarter of the tithe in Žitný ostrov, see <hi
                            rend="smallcap">C. Tóth–Lakatos–Mikó</hi> 2014, 172.</note> aliquas
                    praeterea habere poteris. Vide igitur, ne sis negligens. Nam nunc res agitur in
                    cardine. Si tardus aut negligens eris, damnum irrecuperabile mihi et tibi facere
                    poteris. Si diligens, commodum maximum. Cum <persName>Stephano
                        doctore</persName><del corresp="Olahus">familiariis</del><add
                        corresp="Olahus" type="corr">familiarius</add> loqui poteris, quocum mihi
                    olim fuit magna consuetudo, si ea illi non excidit, quod non credo. Vide, si
                    quid expiscari poteris. Age tamen caute. Vale et de omnibus mihi rescribe, </p>
                <pb facs="15330309_2_2.jpg"/>
                <p xml:id="p.3"><add corresp="Olahus" type="insert">quae</add> egeris, audieris, et
                    intellexeris. Reverendo <persName>domino Agriensi</persName><note
                        xml:id="note.7">Tamás Szalaházy.</note> scribam hoc triduo aut
                        quatriduo.<note xml:id="note.8">This letter is no longer extant.</note></p>
                <p xml:id="p.4"><placeName>Bruxellae</placeName> 9. Martii 1533.</p>
            </div>
